Render the bashly data structure using cutsom templates

Usage:
  bashly render LOCATION [options]
  bashly render (-h|--help)

Options:
  -t --template NAME
    Template name [default: main]

  -w --watch
    Watch bashly.yml and TEMPLATES_ROOT for changes and render on change

  -s --save PATH
    Save the render output to a file

  -h --help
    Show this help

Parameters:
  LOCATION
    An ID to an internal templates root, or a path to a custom templates root.
    
    Available IDs (note the leading colon):
    - :markdown - render markdown documents for each command.

Examples:
  bashly render :markdown
  bashly render /path/to/templates --template main
  bashly render --watch
  bashly render --watch --save docs/index.md
